00:18:35,210 --> 00:18:36,320
Some honey for you.

267
00:18:37,850 --> 00:18:42,990
You know, I just found out yuzu has more vitamins than lemons.

268
00:18:44,420 --> 00:18:47,090
I thought it'd be a good pick-me-up for you.

269
00:18:47,190 --> 00:18:48,360
That's why I wanted to make it.

270
00:18:52,070 --> 00:18:53,100
What was that?

271
00:18:53,170 --> 00:18:55,469
- This is omija. - Omija?

272
00:18:55,470 --> 00:18:57,370
- Do you know what that is? - Omija?

273
00:18:58,340 --> 00:18:59,440
Is that a fruit?

274
00:18:59,510 --> 00:19:03,380
It's a fruit. It's called omija because it has five flavors.

275
00:19:04,940 --> 00:19:07,810
Let me guess. Sweet,

276
00:19:08,650 --> 00:19:10,750
sour, salty?

277
00:19:11,020 --> 00:19:14,550
Sweet, cute, and sexy like me.

278
00:19:15,220 --> 00:19:20,160
- Like me. - No. It's not like that.

279
00:19:29,740 --> 00:19:31,400
You look very professional.

280
00:19:32,570 --> 00:19:35,210
This is a heart for you.

281
00:19:37,940 --> 00:19:39,110
Ta-da!

282
00:19:43,350 --> 00:19:46,790
- Ta-da! Yes. - There's a heart.

283
00:19:47,190 --> 00:19:49,590
You have to mix this, so let me do it for you.

284
00:20:00,130 --> 00:20:01,569
- It's so good. - Really?

285
00:20:01,570 --> 00:20:02,570
Yes, really.

286
00:20:02,571 --> 00:20:05,640
- How is it? - So fresh. I love it.

287
00:20:09,040 --> 00:20:11,840
It's so, so good.

288
00:20:12,310 --> 00:20:13,310
- I like it. - So good?

289
00:20:18,850 --> 00:20:19,850
Thank you.

290
00:20:21,520 --> 00:20:22,960
Is this your first time trying omija?

291
00:20:23,360 --> 00:20:26,060
- Yes. - Really? Want to try some?

292
00:20:31,060 --> 00:20:32,070
How is it?

293
00:20:33,430 --> 00:20:34,430
Good.

294
00:20:35,330 --> 00:20:36,869
How should I describe it? The taste of omija?

295
00:20:36,870 --> 00:20:38,710
It's tangy and...

296
00:20:39,070 --> 00:20:40,640
- Sour? - And sweet.

297
00:20:41,210 --> 00:20:45,180
It has so many different flavors. Is it good as a dessert ingredient?

298
00:20:45,240 --> 00:20:48,650
- I want to give it a try. Yes. - Really?

299
00:20:48,920 --> 00:20:52,950
Then we could make a jam or a preserve,

300
00:20:53,020 --> 00:20:55,050
and it'd be so good inside a dessert.

301
00:20:55,120 --> 00:20:59,060
Maybe we can make...

302
00:20:59,130 --> 00:21:01,630
omija jam.

303
00:21:03,260 --> 00:21:05,300
What's the most popular fruit in Thailand?

304
00:21:05,400 --> 00:21:06,530
Durian.

305
00:21:06,730 --> 00:21:08,530
Durian? I've never had durian before.

306
00:21:08,600 --> 00:21:09,600
Do you like durian?

307
00:21:09,670 --> 00:21:12,310
It smells pretty bad.

308
00:21:12,370 --> 00:21:16,010
But when you eat it, you will love it.

309
00:21:16,080 --> 00:21:17,710
So, so good.

310
00:21:17,980 --> 00:21:19,550
Next time I go to Thailand, let's eat it together.

311
00:21:20,310 --> 00:21:23,049
Sounds good. When you come to Thailand,

312
00:21:23,050 --> 00:21:24,579
- you can call me. Yes. - Really?

313
00:21:24,580 --> 00:21:26,720
I'd love that.

314
00:21:27,550 --> 00:21:28,590
I'd love that.

315
00:21:42,140 --> 00:21:44,040
And then...

316
00:21:44,800 --> 00:21:47,140
For our final mission...

317
00:21:47,210 --> 00:21:50,580
is to include three seasons to a dessert, right?

318
00:21:50,640 --> 00:21:52,580
We have to turn our three seasons into a dessert, right?

319
00:21:52,650 --> 00:21:57,050
What season do you think our relationship is?

320
00:22:00,490 --> 00:22:02,219
For me, it's winter.

321
00:22:02,220 --> 00:22:03,390
- Winter? - Yes.

322
00:22:03,920 --> 00:22:06,930
- Why? - Because I met you in winter.

323
00:22:07,830 --> 00:22:11,760
And this is my first time in Korea.

324
00:22:11,830 --> 00:22:16,570
At first, I thought I was going to be really nervous.

325
00:22:16,640 --> 00:22:20,070
Then we became a team.

326
00:22:20,340 --> 00:22:24,340
It's been so wonderful, and I feel really comfortable.

327
00:22:26,180 --> 00:22:27,980
Do you need a cushion?

328
00:22:29,720 --> 00:22:32,490
- And you go like this. - Okay.

329
00:22:33,950 --> 00:22:34,950
So good.

330
00:22:37,960 --> 00:22:39,260
It's okay.

331
00:22:46,700 --> 00:22:50,770
- I was thinking spring and summer. - Why do you think that?

332
00:22:50,840 --> 00:22:54,010
When you laugh...

333
00:22:54,770 --> 00:22:57,280
or show that bright energy of yours,

334
00:22:57,340 --> 00:23:01,110
it feels as exciting and joyful as spring.

335
00:23:01,180 --> 00:23:04,220
So you're like spring, but at the same time...

336
00:23:05,820 --> 00:23:07,790
Summer is all about passion, you know?

337
00:23:07,850 --> 00:23:11,560
The way we made desserts together felt like summer.

338
00:23:12,560 --> 00:23:16,530
It'd been a while since I'd been that focused.

339
00:23:17,100 --> 00:23:18,970
I think it was the most passionate I've been about anything recently.

340
00:23:19,870 --> 00:23:22,370
And when you're so focused on doing something,

341
00:23:22,840 --> 00:23:24,770
you're even more amazing.

342
00:23:25,370 --> 00:23:27,140
That's why I want to express summer, too.

343
00:23:33,150 --> 00:23:38,380
- I can feel that. - I'm embarrassed.

344
00:23:41,450 --> 00:23:42,760
Is that enough, you think?

345
00:23:42,820 --> 00:23:45,019
- Yes, that's plenty! - Enough?

346
00:23:45,020 --> 00:23:47,359
- Yes. - Okay. To our final mission.

347
00:23:47,360 --> 00:23:49,000
- Cheers! - Cheers!

348
00:23:49,460 --> 00:23:52,000
- Yes. - Yes. Cheers.

349
00:23:52,060 --> 00:23:54,400
- Yes. - Yes.

350
00:23:56,570 --> 00:23:59,270
Since we're here at Seoul Forest,

351
00:24:00,170 --> 00:24:01,610
shall we go take some pictures?

352
00:24:02,010 --> 00:24:04,079
- Sure. Yes. - Shall we?

353
00:24:04,080 --> 00:24:05,140
Let's bundle up.

354
00:24:06,680 --> 00:24:07,749
Thank you.

355
00:24:07,750 --> 00:24:09,079
- So cold. - It's cold.

356
00:24:09,080 --> 00:24:11,219
- Cold. - Cold.

357
00:24:11,220 --> 00:24:13,820
- Let's go take pictures. - Okay. Let's go.

358
00:24:13,890 --> 00:24:16,820
- Go. Let's go. - Let's go.

359
00:25:01,430 --> 00:25:02,870
- Hello. - Hello.

360
00:25:03,240 --> 00:25:05,439
- Hi. - Hi. How are you?

361
00:25:05,440 --> 00:25:06,769
- I'm good. - Good?

362
00:25:06,770 --> 00:25:08,610
- Yes. - Let's take a look around.

363
00:25:08,980 --> 00:25:10,040
Okay.

364
00:25:10,680 --> 00:25:13,209
Lin Lin, have you ever made pottery? Have you?

365
00:25:13,210 --> 00:25:14,279
- This is my first time. - First time?

366
00:25:14,280 --> 00:25:15,750
Will be my first time.

367
00:25:15,820 --> 00:25:19,290
I've wanted to try making pottery for a long time.

368
00:25:19,350 --> 00:25:21,950
If today's the chance, I'm very happy.

369
00:25:22,360 --> 00:25:24,859
When I saw you making cakes,

370
00:25:24,860 --> 00:25:28,390
I figured you'd enjoy making pottery and be good at it.

371
00:25:28,460 --> 00:25:30,960
So I wanted to come here and try it together.

372
00:25:32,800 --> 00:25:35,000
There's so much different pottery.

373
00:25:35,070 --> 00:25:38,699
Isn't that your style? That one, the one that looks like a house.

374
00:25:38,700 --> 00:25:41,409
Yes, right? I think they're pretty similar.

375
00:25:41,410 --> 00:25:44,279
Making pottery and how you decorate your cakes.

376
00:25:44,280 --> 00:25:45,850
They seem really similar.

377
00:25:46,210 --> 00:25:47,910
Lin Lin, is there anything you want to look at?

378
00:26:05,330 --> 00:26:06,630
You'll get hurt.

379
00:26:09,000 --> 00:26:10,069
Cute.

380
00:26:10,070 --> 00:26:12,740
- This is your cake style. - Yes, it is.

381
00:26:12,810 --> 00:26:14,970
We could put an animal on top of this.

382
00:26:15,040 --> 00:26:18,280
- I think you can make this. - I think so.

383
00:26:18,340 --> 00:26:20,050
- Right? - I can try.

384
00:26:20,110 --> 00:26:23,250
You know, it takes a whole month for pottery to be complete.

385
00:26:23,580 --> 00:26:27,820
We didn't get off to a great start when we first met either.

386
00:26:28,390 --> 00:26:30,560
This was the one we found a little disappointing.

387
00:26:31,520 --> 00:26:35,060
The Sunshine Bear made by Lin Lin and Cha Joo Wan.

388
00:26:41,900 --> 00:26:47,509
As time goes by, it can have a really beautiful finish.

389
00:26:47,510 --> 00:26:51,310
I thought our relationship is a lot like making pottery,

390
00:26:51,380 --> 00:26:52,580
so I really wanted to bring you here.

391
00:26:53,050 --> 00:26:55,510
- Okay. - Okay! Let's do this.

392
00:26:56,150 --> 00:26:57,650
- Let's go. - Let's go.

393
00:26:59,890 --> 00:27:02,960
All right. Now, for you, Lin Lin.

394
00:27:03,020 --> 00:27:06,030
How come your apron is dirty and mine is clean?

395
00:27:06,090 --> 00:27:10,100
- Because I... - You're a professional, right?

396
00:27:10,660 --> 00:27:13,070
A princess should wear a clean one.

397
00:27:16,700 --> 00:27:17,770
I remember...

398
00:27:18,270 --> 00:27:19,309
Lin Lin.

399
00:27:19,310 --> 00:27:21,739
I put your apron on for you when we first met.

400
00:27:21,740 --> 00:27:22,910
Yes, I remember.

401
00:27:39,160 --> 00:27:41,360
Lin Lin, have a seat.

402
00:27:41,830 --> 00:27:44,130
This is like the turntable I use when I make cakes.

403
00:27:44,200 --> 00:27:46,800
That I use for my cake as well.

404
00:27:48,400 --> 00:27:52,300
I have a feeling you're going to be better at this than me.

405
00:27:52,510 --> 00:27:56,340
We're going to make a cup today.

406
00:27:57,310 --> 00:28:02,409
We'll shape the cup together. I already shaped one.

407
00:28:02,410 --> 00:28:06,490
I made a pretty big cup. If you bring your hands,

408
00:28:06,650 --> 00:28:08,320
the clay narrows inward.

409
00:28:08,550 --> 00:28:12,190
Now, what if you do the opposite? Go up instead.

410
00:28:12,730 --> 00:28:15,660
- Press? - Yes, gently. Not too hard.

411
00:28:15,830 --> 00:28:19,060
Like you're holding a newborn. With love.

412
00:28:20,070 --> 00:28:22,129
- Don't let it lose its shape. - Okay.

413
00:28:22,130 --> 00:28:23,240
Here, give me your hands.

414
00:28:23,300 --> 00:28:25,240
With this hand, you hold it steady from the bottom.

415
00:28:25,300 --> 00:28:29,310
- Go up. - And with this hand...

416
00:28:29,380 --> 00:28:31,140
Be confident. You're Lin Lin.

417
00:28:31,510 --> 00:28:33,280
That's really good.

418
00:28:33,510 --> 00:28:35,480
Hold it steady. Now pull up. That's perfect.

419
00:28:37,120 --> 00:28:39,620
Okay, now you're going to bring the top in a little bit, too.

420
00:28:40,190 --> 00:28:41,720
- Bring it in? - Yes.

421
00:28:47,430 --> 00:28:49,360
Oh, my. You're getting the hang of it.

422
00:28:50,530 --> 00:28:52,929
This can't be your first time? It really doesn't seem like it.

423
00:28:52,930 --> 00:28:54,769
- I think you've been practicing. - Here?

424
00:28:54,770 --> 00:28:56,039
You nailed it.

425
00:28:56,040 --> 00:28:59,070
- Brown. Yes, it's brown. - You're a natural.

426
00:28:59,140 --> 00:29:02,340
Mine are still a bit crooked. You're good at this.

427
00:29:06,380 --> 00:29:07,750
I'm making it taller.

428
00:29:08,410 --> 00:29:10,080
Nice shape!

429
00:29:10,580 --> 00:29:13,890
- Wait, I just want to do shapes. - You want it to be round?

430
00:29:15,990 --> 00:29:17,990
So what do you think of pottery? Is it fun, Lin Lin?

431
00:29:18,060 --> 00:29:21,530
Yes, it's fun. I love making art.

432
00:29:35,770 --> 00:29:40,180
You started making desserts as a hobby, right?

433
00:29:40,250 --> 00:29:41,980
That's right. It was a hobby at first.

434
00:29:42,050 --> 00:29:46,250
It was therapeutic. It's stress-free.

435
00:29:46,320 --> 00:29:51,060
But once I started getting orders, it wasn't therapeutic anymore.

436
00:29:51,220 --> 00:29:54,460
- It's very stressful. - All of a sudden.

437
00:29:55,530 --> 00:29:57,460
That's so cool. I want to be like that too.

438
00:29:57,530 --> 00:29:59,770
- You're my role model. - Thank you.

439
00:29:59,830 --> 00:30:01,500
Lin Lin, my role model.

440
00:30:01,870 --> 00:30:05,440
It'd be great if I started pottery and got flooded with orders too.

441
00:30:05,500 --> 00:30:08,840
Do you sell pottery?

442
00:30:09,070 --> 00:30:14,280
No, I don't sell them. I make things like cups and plates,

443
00:30:14,910 --> 00:30:19,120
- spoon rests... stuff like that. - Nice.

444
00:30:21,520 --> 00:30:23,520
I think this is pretty much done,

445
00:30:23,590 --> 00:30:26,230
and I want us to leave our mark on this cup.

446
00:30:26,630 --> 00:30:29,930
I'm going to put my hand over yours. Right here.

447
00:30:32,770 --> 00:30:35,230
Let's hold your right hand and mine together like this,

448
00:30:35,300 --> 00:30:38,899
- press them against the pottery. - Okay. Do I press now?

449
00:30:38,900 --> 00:30:42,340
When you press, with confidence. One, two, three.

450
00:30:43,610 --> 00:30:45,310
Okay.

451
00:30:48,680 --> 00:30:51,920
And there it is. Our first memory.

452
00:30:51,980 --> 00:30:53,420
While making this pottery.

453
00:30:53,890 --> 00:30:54,890
Good story.

454
00:30:54,891 --> 00:30:56,790
- Right. For the story. - I like it.

455
00:30:56,860 --> 00:30:58,720
Time to decorate. Your favorite part.

456
00:30:59,730 --> 00:31:01,560
First, our names.

457
00:31:02,700 --> 00:31:04,030
I have an idea.

458
00:31:05,830 --> 00:31:06,830
Like this.

459
00:31:06,900 --> 00:31:08,230
It's a game.

460
00:31:09,230 --> 00:31:11,339
I'm X, you're O.

461
00:31:11,340 --> 00:31:12,370
- Okay. - Okay?

462
00:31:12,440 --> 00:31:15,010
If I have three Xs in a row, I win.

463
00:31:15,070 --> 00:31:17,440
- I start first. - Start.

464
00:31:18,410 --> 00:31:19,880
Okay, I start here. X.

465
00:31:20,710 --> 00:31:21,850
Your turn.

466
00:31:22,380 --> 00:31:23,420
O.

467
00:31:24,220 --> 00:31:25,480
Okay.

468
00:31:26,290 --> 00:31:27,650
X.

469
00:31:27,720 --> 00:31:29,560
Why the O look like that?

470
00:31:34,760 --> 00:31:36,200
A heart.

471
00:31:36,260 --> 00:31:37,660
DIdn't I win with a heart?

472
00:31:46,710 --> 00:31:50,880
For the upcoming mission, did you get some ideas?

473
00:31:50,940 --> 00:31:53,379
- I have an idea. - Okay, tell me.

474
00:31:53,380 --> 00:31:56,320
I'll let you know and you can share your ideas.

475
00:31:56,580 --> 00:31:59,619
For the third mission, we have to make three desserts.

476
00:31:59,620 --> 00:32:00,989
But I was thinking...

477
00:32:00,990 --> 00:32:05,159
instead of a season like winter, spring, or summer...

478
00:32:05,160 --> 00:32:08,860
but more like a season of love.

479
00:32:11,260 --> 00:32:13,830
I want it to be a dessert that leaves a lingering feeling.

480
00:32:13,900 --> 00:32:16,870
A sweet flavor...

481
00:32:16,940 --> 00:32:18,740
Like it lingers in the mouth.

482
00:32:19,340 --> 00:32:21,840
- Good idea? That's great. - Good idea.

483
00:32:22,110 --> 00:32:23,180
You're a genius.

484
00:32:25,480 --> 00:32:30,880
The other teams will probably represent the seasons literally.

485
00:32:31,250 --> 00:32:33,620
I feel like your idea...

486
00:32:34,120 --> 00:32:36,859
is very unique. I love it.

487
00:32:36,860 --> 00:32:40,289
- I love being unique. - Thank you.

488
00:32:40,290 --> 00:32:42,360
I just hope the judges will get it.

489
00:32:42,730 --> 00:32:45,000
Sometimes, I feel like they don't understand my intentions.

490
00:32:46,130 --> 00:32:48,330
No. That's not the case.

491
00:32:48,530 --> 00:32:50,099
We'll win this time.

492
00:32:50,100 --> 00:32:51,740
I'm happy that you understand me.

493
00:32:52,600 --> 00:32:56,280
Let's just enjoy this moment together.

494
00:32:56,340 --> 00:32:58,980
We're having fun doing something...

495
00:32:59,040 --> 00:33:01,149
and spending time together.

496
00:33:01,150 --> 00:33:03,380
- Let's cheer for the last mission. - Let's do this.

497
00:33:07,290 --> 00:33:11,060
The cup we made will take a month to be done.

498
00:33:11,290 --> 00:33:15,660
It will be shipped to your home.

499
00:33:15,690 --> 00:33:19,530
It's a bummer to leave empty-handed as we came all the way here.

500
00:33:19,770 --> 00:33:21,600
So I've prepared a gift for you.

501
00:33:27,340 --> 00:33:30,879
- You prepared something for me. - You made this?

502
00:33:30,880 --> 00:33:34,210
- Really? - I made this. Take a look.

503
00:33:37,950 --> 00:33:39,450
So cute.

504
00:33:45,360 --> 00:33:46,360
One side.

505
00:33:48,890 --> 00:33:50,160
The back.

506
00:33:52,130 --> 00:33:53,900
E.T.

507
00:33:53,970 --> 00:33:56,099
Thank you. You wrote your name too.

508
00:33:56,100 --> 00:33:57,170
This...

509
00:33:57,600 --> 00:33:58,639
Bite Me Sweet.

510
00:33:58,640 --> 00:34:00,770
- Bite Me Sweet. - Bite moi.

511
00:34:02,940 --> 00:34:05,740
My mistake. Sorry. But it came from the heart.

512
00:34:05,810 --> 00:34:09,620
Joo Wan. The sun on this is me.

513
00:34:09,680 --> 00:34:13,389
- And the pink on the outside... - It is you.

514
00:34:13,390 --> 00:34:15,050
is because you like pink,

515
00:34:15,120 --> 00:34:17,420
- so I painted it pink. - Amazing.

516
00:34:17,590 --> 00:34:19,159
- Really? - Yes, really.

517
00:34:19,160 --> 00:34:21,460
- Now... - Good. I like it?

518
00:34:21,530 --> 00:34:23,500
- I like it? - You like it?

519
00:34:23,930 --> 00:34:24,930
- I'm glad you like it. - I love it!

520
00:34:24,931 --> 00:34:28,630
- Team... - Team Fresh.

521
00:34:28,900 --> 00:34:31,240
Lin Lin, let's go to Singapore together.

522
00:34:31,300 --> 00:34:32,470
- Let's go. - Let's do it.

523
00:34:32,540 --> 00:34:33,740
- Let's do it. - Let's do it.

524
00:34:33,810 --> 00:34:35,210
Let's do it.

525
00:34:45,350 --> 00:34:46,990
What is this place?

526
00:34:47,650 --> 00:34:49,790
It's winter sea.

527
00:34:50,060 --> 00:34:51,920
